sentences: Formed in 2001 by Daniel Plant (guitars), Ed Godby (vocals), Mark Lyons (guitars), Will Shaw (drums) and David Hopkinson (bass), they played a mix of metalcore, noise rock and progressive metal.
They toured the UK and Europe with Killswitch Engage, Norma Jean and Darkest Hour.
After the recording of a five-track demo CD, the band released the Resention Is a Big Word in a Small Town EP for Nottingham-based In at the Deep End Records in 2002.
This was followed by the album Breaking The Fourth Wall in 2003 on Calculated Risk Records.
After much critical acclaim, and a lot of touring, the band signed with Earache Records in 2004.
Earache re-released Breaking The Fourth Wall in 2005 with six bonus tracks.
2005 also saw the release of Beecher's second full-length album This Elegy, His Autopsy.
This album, as well as being released as a standard CD, was also released as a limited edition vinyl box-set (limited to 1000 copies).
The band's breakup was announced in January 2006, and the final show was at the Star and Garter in Manchester on 2 February 2006, playing alongside Narcosis and D-Rail.

Daniel Shaw currently plays in Wode and his new band Aggressive Perfector.
The band briefly reformed during December 2010-June 2011, for a one-off ten-year anniversary show at Manchester's Moho Live with support from Trojan Horse and Nasdaq.
However, after they finished the planned shows in late June 2011 they announced they were no plans to make the reunion permanent.
